SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 245
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Cooper Townley, 2025
Salutatorian of Hardin County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Townley is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
Salutatorian of the 2025 graduating class at Hardin County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Townley has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Cooper Townley has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Townley's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride
for his family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2025 Hardin
County High School Salutatorian, Cooper Townley, on his impressive academic achievement
and extend to him our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
